<subSubSection id="C32EC7FEBA6E9D00FD37FC4EFE99FEDB" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B9475BA6E9D07FD37FC4EFB2EFB80" blockId="27.[699,1228,809,1742]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Farkas cited the AMNH numbers of the 
<typeStatus id="548F2AD7BA6E9D07FB4BFC6CFCBBFC38" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">holotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus id="548F2AD7BA6E9D07FC80FC09FC69FC38" box="[879,982,985,1008]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">paratype</typeStatus>
, AMNH 580866, an adult female collected by Last at the same locality. Only these 
<specimenCount id="9D325FFCBA6E9D07FC5EFBC4FBDEFBE3" box="[945,1121,1044,1067]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
came to AMNH with the Rothschild Collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B9475BA6E9D07FD37FB9EFBF6F990" blockId="27.[699,1228,809,1742]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
The collector’s name as written on the Rothschild label appears to be ‘‘Zaast’’ and was so published by Farkas. In a fascinating piece of ornithological detective work, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6E9D07FB6DFB76FC0FFB13" author="Collar, N. J. &amp; I. Tattersall" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="55 - 59" refId="ref92177" refString="Collar, N. J., and I. Tattersall. 1987. J. T. Last and the type-locality of Benson's Rockthrush Monticola bensoni. Bulletin of the British Ornithologists' Club 107: 55 - 59." type="journal article" year="1987">Collar and Tattersall (1987)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6E9D07FC03FB14FB34FB13" author="Collar, N. J." box="[1004,1163,1220,1243]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="151" refId="ref92039" refString="Collar, N. J. 1999. The type locality and conservation status of Monticola bensoni (letter to the editor). Ostrich 70: 151." type="journal article" year="1999">Collar (1999)</bibRefCitation>
have uncovered details of Last’s travels and the collecting date and locality coordinates of the 
<specimenCount id="9D325FFCBA6E9D07FD54FACCFCD0FAFB" box="[699,879,1308,1331]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
listed above. They showed that Ankarefo (modern spelling) was at about 238219S, 448489E and that the 
<typeStatus id="548F2AD7BA6E9D07FBC0FA86FBDEFAA5" box="[1071,1121,1366,1389]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
material was collected in either 1891 or 1892. They also listed a bibliography of five articles written by Last about his travels and collections in 
<collectingCountry id="F323D4E5BA6E9D07FD35FA1CFCD7FA2B" box="[730,872,1484,1507]" name="Madagascar" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Rothschild apparently bought specimens, either from Last directly or through a dealer. The name on the Rothschild label must have been misinterpreted from a list accompanying the specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B9475BA6E9D00FD37F98EFE99FEDB" blockId="27.[699,1228,809,1742]" lastBlockId="28.[124,653,193,275]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
See 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6E9D07FCFFF98EFBD6F9BD" author="Goodman, S. M. &amp; L. A. Weigt" box="[784,1129,1630,1653]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="26 - 35" refId="ref94203" refString="Goodman, S. M., and L. A. Weigt. 2002. The generic and species relationships of the reputed endemic Malagasy genus Pseudocossyphus (family Turdidae). Ostrich 73: 26 - 35." type="journal article" year="2002">Goodman and Weigt (2002)</bibRefCitation>
for the results of their molecular studies and a summary of previous taxonomic treatments. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA5E984BA6E9D07FD54F966FC73F905" author="Dickinson, E. C." box="[699,972,1718,1741]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref93312" refString="Dickinson, E. C. (editor). 2003. The Howard and Moore complete checklist of the birds of the world. 3 rd ed. London: Christopher Helm, 1039 pp." type="book" year="2003">Dickinson (2003: 688)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA6E9D07FBDCF967FB32F906" authorityName="Farkas" authorityYear="1971" box="[1075,1165,1719,1742]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Monticola" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bensoni">
<emphasis id="B9404867BA6E9D07FBDCF967FB32F906" box="[1075,1165,1719,1742]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">bensoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA699D00FEC6FF11FDE8FF10" baseAuthorityName="G. R. Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[297,599,193,216]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Pseudocossyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sharpei">
<emphasis id="B9404867BA699D00FEC6FF11FDE8FF10" box="[297,599,193,216]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Pseudocossyphus sharpei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and placed it in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA699D00FE43FF0EFD88FF3D" authorityName="Vigors" authorityYear="1825" box="[428,567,222,245]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Saxicolinae">Saxicolinae</taxonomicName>
, family 
<taxonomicName id="4C34EFF6BA699D00FF93FF2CFE9EFEDB" authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1822" box="[124,289,252,275]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Muscicapidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
